comments: Diallo (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Dinwiddie's (WAS) path and does not deliver contact.
Cunningham (DET) reaches in and places his hand on top of the ball after Beal's (WAS) gather. Cunningham's hand remains on the ball as Beal returns to the floor. A held ball is correctly whistled.
Gafford (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Diallo's (DET) path and makes marginal contact as he disengages.
Diallo (DET) and Caldwell-Pope (WAS) briefly engage in marginal contact prior to disengaging during the loose ball.
Stewart (DET) grabs Gafford's (WAS) jersey during the rebound and the contact affects his ability to move freely.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) and Grant (DET) briefly engage in marginal contact off ball prior to separating.

Replay review of the foul called on Caldwell-Pope (WAS) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed successful. Caldwell-Pope (WAS) swipes down and makes incidental hand on ball contact which dislodges it from Grant (DET) during his driving shot attempt.
Stewart (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Caldwell-Pope's (WAS) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Kuzma (WAS) makes marginal contact with Grant (DET) off ball that does not affect his ability to get to the pass.
Kuzma (WAS) makes incidental contact with Grant's (DET) arm after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Gafford (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Diallo's (DET) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Stewart (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Caldwell-Pope's (WAS) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Stewart (DET) is in the lane for longer than three seconds prior to his shot attempt near the rim.
Kuzma (WAS) places his arm to Stewart's (DET) side and marginal contact occurs during his shot attempt near the rim.
Jackson (DET) makes contact with Caldwell-Pope's (WAS) arm during his drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Dinwiddie (WAS) makes contact with Jackson (DET) off ball that does not affect his ability to defend the pass.
Diallo (DET) reaches in and makes marginal contact to Beal's (WAS) arm that does not affect his ability to maintain control of the ball.
Correctly called backcourt violation on Beal (WAS).
Jackson (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Kuzma's (WAS) path and does not deliver contact.
Stewart (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Gafford's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Dinwiddie (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position during Grant's (DET) jump shot attempt. Grant's reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
WAS signals a timeout with the count being under 5 seconds.
Diallo (DET) and Beal (WAS) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Beal (WAS) does not abnormally or overtly extend his leg into Grant (DET), and the contact is marginal.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) is already in Diallo's (DET) path and is firming up when marginal contact occurs.
Jackson (DET) places his hand to Beal's (WAS) side during his drive to the basket and marginal contact occurs.
Kuzma (WAS) places his forearm to Cunningham's (DET) side after his gather and marginal contact occurs.
Gafford (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Diallo's (DET) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Stewart (DET) grabs Gafford's (WAS) jersey during the rebound and the contact affects his ability to move freely.
Stewart (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Caldwell-Pope's (WAS) path and does not deliver contact.
Gafford (DET) moves along Cunningham's (DET) path defending his driving shot attempt and the contact is marginal.
Gafford (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Diallo's (DET) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Diallo (DET) makes marginal contact with Beal's (WAS) arm after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Stewart (DET) and Gafford (WAS) mutually engage in marginal contact prior to separating during the made jump shot attempt.
Kuzma (DET) and Grant (DET) briefly engage in incidental contact off ball while the jump shot attempt is airborne. Kuzma does not dislodge Grant.
Grant (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Dinwiddie's (WAS) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Gafford (WAS) moves laterally against  Cunningham's (DET) path and marginal contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Gafford (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Diallo's (DET) path and he releases away from the contact.
